variable_name usage everywhere
log_dataframe() examples using:

response_id_column
observed_column
variable_name / variable_name_column
message_column where relevant




6.3 Improve method docstrings
We decided docstrings should clearly explain:
For ExceptionLogger.log_dataframe()

when to use variable_name
when to use variable_name_column
that response_id_column is a DataFrame column selector
that observed_column is a DataFrame column selector
that expected is constant for the validation call

For EventLogger.log_dataframe()

message vs message_column
response_id_column
optional variable_name vs variable_name_column


7) Items Explicitly Not Being Changed Right Now
These are important so implementation doesn’t drift.

7.1 No log_many() for EventLogger
We explicitly decided:

do not add log_many() to EventLogger


7.2 No expected_column for now
We explicitly decided:

do not add expected_column right now

Because most current validations have a constant expected value.

7.3 No overloaded response_id / observed in log_dataframe()
We explicitly decided:

do not overload response_id in log_dataframe()
do not overload observed in log_dataframe()

Instead, use:

response_id_column
observed_column


7.4 Do not rename variable_name_column
We explicitly decided:

keep variable_name_column
do not rename to variable_column_names


7.5 No UUIDv7 migration right now
We explicitly decided:

stay on uuid.uuid4() for now


7.6 Return type behavior stays unchanged for now
We did not finalize a change to make all methods return counts.
So for now, the safe assumption is:

keep existing return behavior unless implementation reveals a compelling reason to change it

Meaning
This is effectively a deferred / no-change item for now.

